The New York Stock Exchange said it hasasked members and member firms to refrain from using the NYSEorder delivery system for purposes of executing index arbitragerelated transactions or any other aspect of program tradingafter today's opening.    The request came in a letter issued by the NYSE earlierthis morning.    The Exchange said the order delivery system allows memberfirms to directly route orders to the specialist on the tradingfloor via computer. Reuter&#3;